==English==

===Etymology===
Named after the inventor, the industrial chemist [[w:Ernst Büchner|Ernst Büchner]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|chemistry}} A piece of [[laboratory]] equipment used for [[filtration]]; it is a ceramic funnel with a flat base on which the filter paper is laid flat; normally used with a [[vacuum pump]].

